## Formula Variable Syntax — The Standard

**Rule: Formula expressions and conditions MUST use direct JavaScript variable access. `{{path}}` is NOT supported in formula expressions.**

### Named scopes available in every formula expression
| Scope | Example | Source |
|---|---|---|
| `variables['UUID']` | `variables['d9e0f1a2-...'] === 'shipping'` | `config/variables.json` |
| `collections['UUID']?.data.*` | `collections['a1b2...']?.data?.activeOrder?.totalQuantity > 0` | `config/datasources.json` |
| `context?.item?.data.*` | `context?.item?.data?.productAsset?.preview` | repeat-item scope |
| `globalContext?.browser?.query.*` | `globalContext?.browser?.query?.sort === 'name-asc'` | URL query params |
| `auth?.user`, `auth?.token` | `auth?.user === null` | auth state |
| `_workflow?.lastAction`, `_workflow?.lastError` | `_workflow?.lastError` | workflow state |
| `local?.data?.form?.fields?.field?.isValid` | `local?.data?.form?.fields?.email?.isValid` | form validation state |
| `_conventions?.sortInputMap` | `lookupMap(_conventions?.sortInputMap, globalContext?.browser?.query?.sort, ...)` | engine computed |
| `get('flatKey')` | `get('collectionPageSize')` | arbitrary state path escape hatch |

### In formula/condition expressions
```json
// ✅ CORRECT — direct variable access
"condition": "variables['d9e0f1a2-b3c4-5678-defa-789012345678'] === 'shipping'"
"condition": "variables['UUID'] >= 60"
"value": { "formula": "variables['UUID'] + 1" }
"condition": "collections['UUID']?.data?.activeOrder?.totalQuantity > 0"
"condition": "context?.item?.data?.productAsset?.preview"
"condition": "globalContext?.browser?.query?.sort === 'name-asc'"
"condition": "auth?.user === null"
```

### In text template values
Text nodes (`"text": "..."`) use `{{variables['UUID']}}` interpolation (handled by the text template engine — separate from formula expressions):
```json
// ✅ CORRECT — text template
"text": "{{variables['UUID']}}"
"text": "{{collections['UUID'].data.product.name}}"
"text": "{{context.item.data.productName}}"
```

### For new page-scoped variables
Declare all variables in `config/variables.json` with a UUID. Never use screen `state` for mutable values.
```json
// ✅ Declare in config/variables.json
"UUID": { "label": "Show Address Form", "type": "boolean", "initialValue": false, "folder": "Account" }
// Use in formula expression:
"condition": "variables['UUID']"
// Use in text template:
"text": "{{variables['UUID']}}"
```

**Folder convention:** Group by page/feature name — `"folder": "Account"`, `"folder": "Checkout"`, `"folder": "Product"`, etc.

